reactor.io.queue

Class PersistentQueue<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractQueue<T>
        • reactor.io.queue.PersistentQueue<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<T>, Collection<T>, Queue<T>, CompletableQueue<T>

    public class PersistentQueue<T>
extends AbstractQueue<T>
implements CompletableQueue<T>
    A PersistentQueue is a Queue implementation that delegates the actual storage of the elements in the queue to a QueuePersistor.
    Author:
    Jon Brisbin, Stephane Maldini
